    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": "### Problem\n\nDuring config loading, running nvim_buf_get_lines() on buffer 1 returns a nil result.\n\nSeems to be related to this: https://github.com/neovim/neovim/blob/0aa7d2f4d546647e0d6b5c338bd5517675e9842c/src/nvim/api/buffer.c#L292\n\n### Steps to reproduce\n\nRun `nvim --clean -u` with the below init:\n\n```lua\nprint(\"Buf 1 lines: \", vim.inspect(vim.api.nvim_buf_get_lines(1, 0, -1, false)))\n```\n\n\"Buf 1 lines:\" displays nil.\n\n### Expected behavior\n\nOn e572c9c (right before problem commit 0aa7d2f) , \"Buf 1 lines:\" shows an empty table (no `\"\"` value), which matches the function documentation for an unloaded buffer.\n\n### Nvim version (nvim -v)\n\nCommit 0aa7d2f\n\n### Vim (not Nvim) behaves the same?\n\nN/A\n\n### Operating system/version\n\nLinux Mint 22.1\n\n### Terminal name/version\n\nGhostty 1.2.3\n\n### $TERM environment variable\n\ntmux-256color\n\n### Installation\n\nBuild from repo.",
